'''Volbeat''' is a four-piece [[Denmark|Danish]] [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] band formed in [[Copenhagen]] in 2001. As of 2008, their formation consists of vocalist and guitarist [[Michael Poulsen]], guitarist [[Thomas Bredahl]], bassist [[Anders Kj<U+00F8>lholm]] and drummer [[Jon Larsen]]. The band has released three [[studio album]]s, six [[Single (music)|singles]], one [[DVD]] and two [[Demo (music)|demos]].

They have received ten nominations for the Danish Metal Awards and won three trophies. Volbeat also received four nominations for the [[Danish Music Awards]] but went home empty handed. They also won a [[Steppeulv]] award in 2006, a P3 Guld award in 2007 and a Zulu Award in 2008.

== Danish Metal Awards ==
The Danish Metal Awards is an annual awards ceremony established in 2004 by various Danish metal magazines and TV shows. Volbeat have received three awards from eleven nominations.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dmea.dk/site/2005.html |title=VINDERE OG NOMINEREDE I 2005 |accessdate=2008-09-02 |publisher=dmea.dk |language=Danish }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://dmea.dk/site/2006.html |title=Vindere og nominerede i 2006 |accessdate=2008-09-02 |publisher=dmea.dk  |language=Danish }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://dmea.dk/site/2007.html |title=VINDERE OG NOMINEREDE I 2007 |accessdate=2008-09-02 |publisher=dmea.dk  |language=Danish }}</ref> The band received four nominations for the 2008 edition and won two awards.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=108986 |title=METALLICA, VOLBEAT, SCAMP Honored At DANISH METAL AWARDS |accessdate=2008-11-16 |publisher=Blabbermouth.net }}</ref>

